messages.message: Hey Austria! I know AT is one of the least successful alliances in the game, so I'm super down to work together here, especially if we can get Russia and Turkey fighting.
Hey Germany! Just reaching out to say I think our two nations tend to benefit a ton from working together, and I'm very down to work together if you'd be interested!
Hey Italy! I think our two nations tend to do best when we can leave each other alone, so I'd love it if we could agree to not harass one another?
Hey France, absolutely! Are you up for a DMZ in Burgundy?
Hey Russia, just wanna say good luck and hopefully we can be friends!
I'm also down! Have you heard from either of them yet?
Hey France! I think we both have bigger concerns than each other so I'd like to propose an alliance between us. Would you be willing to agree to a DMZ in the Channel?
Hi Russia, good luck this game! Would you be interested in working together? Do you want to bounce Galicia?
Hey Austria! Just checking in. If there's anything I can do for you, feel free to ask!
Hey Italy! Just wanted to get things going. Let me know if there's anything I can do for you.
Hey Austria, just wanna say good luck and hopefully we can be friends!

Hey England! I'm more than happy to agree to that, I think our nations tend to do best when we don't harass one another. Would you like to focus together on attacking Germany, or would you rather move in separate directions?
Hey Germany! Just wanted to get things started here. If there's anything I can do for you, let me know!
I agree! I love playing as Italy, so I have no interest in causing problems for France and vice versa.
Hey, thanks for the offer! Will do.
Hey Italy, just wanna say good luck and hopefully we can be friends!
Thanks Turkey! I'm definitely down for that.
Hey Russia! I love an R/I, and I think it's one of the more effective alliances in the game. What do you say we work together to take out Turkey and then Austria?
Hey Russia! I'd like to take Norway this year, but I'm not planning on sending any further units your way. If there's anything I can do to help you, feel free to ask!
Hey England, that's great to hear! Good luck this game, let's stay in touch
Cheers!
Turkey messaged me just to wish me luck, nothing really consequential. Have you heard from them?
Hi Turkey! Thanks for reaching out. I definitely hope so too, but I understand that you can't just be friends with everyone. What are you thinking about for a strategy in the Balkans?
Absolutely! I'm glad we could come to an agreement so quickly, I look forward to our alliance!
Have you heard from Russia yet?

Excellent! I feel the same way, so I look forward to our alliance!

Would you be alright with a DMZ in Pie, Gol, and W Med?
Hey England, sounds good to me! If you wouldn't mind convoying over rather than sending an army, that'd make me feel much better :)
I've heard from them, but nothing super substantial. They just wished me luck
I'm gonna move for Bulgaria for now. Are you moving for Austria?
Hey Italy, sounds good to me! I agree, IR is quite nice :)
I don't think I can do that; it would leave me completely open to France. However, I am planning on taking it with a fleet.
Hey Austria, sounds good to me! Bounce Galicia and work together sounds good to me, I think the R/A is one of the more powerful alliances on the board.
I'd be super down for that. I don't see any point in either of us moving there, and it just ties up a unit for each of us that we can use elsewhere.
Not sure yet. I definitely don't want to attack Austria and get stuck on 4 centres.
I have. He wants me to not take Norway with an army. Which is fine by me but I'm not going to oblige. What do you think of him?
Fair enough, as long as it's with a fleet, that works well!
Thanks England! And same for you.
Let's do an E/F against Germany. I'd like a second build this year, though. Do you mind supporting me into Belgium?
Hey Germany! Just wanted to say hi. Let me know if there's anything I can do for you.
Okay!
Hey Turkey, same to you! Best of luck and hopefully we can be friends too :)
Good luck!
Yeah, I think so too! What do you think Turkey will do?
I've heard from Russia too now, they seem willing to work together
How do you want to split the Balkans?
No problem, I can support you into Belgium from Picardy!
Exactly my thoughts!
Well, like any Russian player I would be concerned about a strong North opening from him.
Hey Germany, best of luck! How's it going?
Sure thing. What do you make of Russia?

England is trying to convince me to attack you, and I want to give you the heads up since England has a very clear interest in Germany being destroyed, he's even asking for me to support him into Belgium this year.
He seems willing to cooperate with me at least. He probably wants to avoid conflict in the north at all costs.
Excellent. Are you thinking of opening into Burgundy?
I wonder if we could talk Germany into bouncing him out of Sweden.
I think Turkey will open standard and then decide from there. Maybe see where Italy is going, take advantage of that?
I'm actually going to open into Picardy. From there I can support you into Belgium, and I can also keep Germany out of Burgundy, and then next year we can move in on him.
Hey Germany, just wanted to wish you good luck! I'm thinking we might want to cooperate this game, maybe team up to fight off a potential juggernaut
That would be interesting, let's see what they say.
I'm not sure, what are you thinking?
Hey Austria, agreed! I'd like to stay friendly, we're both in tough spots
Turkey did message me to wish me luck and tell me we could be friends. So I think he might move to the Black Sea.
I'll shoot him a message. I'd like to see a strong Austria this game.
Great! I think Russia is going to try and stay friendly with both of us at first, and that's a dangerous game.
What are your feelings about Greece?
Same, thanks!
Hey Italy, good luck this game! I'd love if you and Austria stayed friendly
What are you thinking for a strategy in the Balkans?
Interesting, I appreciate the heads up. Let me try to get more information
I was thinking Greece and Serbia for me, and Bulgaria and Rumania for you. Do you want to work against Russia?
That sounds like a good plan. Germany should fall rather quickly.
Seems pretty friendly so far, hopefully we can stay on good terms. What are you thinking?
Sounds good, and no problem!
How do you want to approach Turkey?
Hey Russia, same to you!
I'd like to take him out, but of course the first move is crucial and Black Sea would be a good sign for that.
Thanks, hope we can have a nice peaceful border between us :)
Agreed!
I think Italy is also interested in taking Turkey out, which would be great.
Hey Austria! I know we're not super close to each other at the moment, but I just wanted to reach out and say I'm always open to communication if you'd like to work together at all in the future!
I think we should open standard, I'll try to get into Galicia and secure Rum, you should go for Bul and then see what happens.
Yeah, he messaged me that too! Which is good, gives us all options :)
Perfect

Hey Russia! I know we're not super close to each other at the moment, but I just wanted to reach out and say I'm always open to communication if you'd like to work together at all in the future! I've also heard some talk about England wanting to focus on Scandinavia early, and I wanted to give you the heads up.
Yeah me too! I'll see what I can do.
That works for me. I can't immediately go against Russia but after a few turns maybe
Hey France, I appreciate it! And I will definitely keep that in mind. Do you think you're going to work with Germany or England?
Awesome! Do you want to work with Austria for the time being, and take out Turkey first?
Are you gonna be going against Italy?
He seems noncommital. I don't know what to make of him. I'd like to keep him out of Sweden if possible. I think it'd help both of us.
So are you thinking a standard Lepanto?
I'm not super interested in it myself, but I don't want to see Austria in there.
Hey France, best of luck and thanks for the heads up! Always open to communicating, and I'm also super open to working together if the opportunity presents itself!
Are we gonna bounce black sea?
No, not at first, probably once I pick up my first or second build.
Yeah, that would be perfect! We've already established a good relationship.
That's what I'm thinking. I know Turkey's going for Bulgaria, so it shouldn't be too hard to take him out
Good! I just got the same message. I think he is just going for Tunis this year, but maybe he will commit against Turkey after that.
Sounds good, best of luck to you as well! And I'd love to work together if the opportunity presents itself!
Sounds good!
Awesome! Just to be clear, you're focusing on securing the north before moving south? If so, I think we should be good
Ok cool
How about you, what are you thinking?
Might as well, good way to ensure neither of us takes it.
Awesome! How do you want to play the first few turns? I'll go for the standard lepanto opening, but apart from that we should think about how to maximise our units
Sounds good to me! Yeah, I assume he'll be waiting to see how this first move goes.
Honestly I'm not sure yet, I'm going to see how this first turn plays out and go from there. Have you decided on who you're going to work with yet?
Ok
I'm thinking Vienna to Galicia and Budapest to Serbia. Have you decided what to do with Venice?
Yeah, me and England will establish a peaceful border and I'll secure Rum. We'll see how the next year goes, but taking Turkey should be fairly simple :)
I would assume so.
Perfect. I'll open standard lepanto, and hopefully Austria and Turkey fight.
Have you decided what to do about the Black Sea?
Agreed. If he opens south, are you thinking of convoying to Norway?
I haven't decided yet
Awesome! Have you heard much from the east?
Yep, Turkey wants to bounce, should I let him in?
I'll probably just leave it in Venice. I can't really move it anywhere that won't compromise our position. I definitely don't want to leave it, but I also don't want to antagonize France
I see, have you heard from Russia? Are you thinking of going to the Black Sea?
I would bounce, but that's just me.
Have you heard much from the west? I'd rather not have Germany try and interfere with us
Also, do you mind if I ask if you're going to bounce in Black Sea?
Russia and I are bouncing the black sea
Just to be safe
Are you planning to go against Austria?
Not really, there isn't really anyone who is committed to an alliance with me at this point.
True, it's a bit too risky to let Turkey in, and even if I was working with him, I'd rather not leave Sev open.
Yes, that's the plan :)
Yeah, I think I agree with that. I've only talked to Germany briefly, we just wanted to be friendly.
Yep, that's the plan!
How about you?
That makes sense
Yeah, that's what I've gotten from them too. I was worried that they might want to move south.
That's fair, what do you think he will do with his other unit?
Perfect!
They agreed to stay friendly. Have they talked to you about what they're going to do about England and France?
I'm not planning on it. I'll be taking it with a fleet.
Ok cool. I'm gonna work with Austria for a few turns but once you get into position I'll move for Greece
Same, my choice is really between England and Germany. England wants me to attack Germany with him, while Germany is more suspicious of England.
You?
And then after that we can split Austria
No, I've actually only spoken to England, Germany, and Austria so far. You?
Got it, sounds good
I've spoken to everyone now lol
No, not really. They just said they'd like for us to stay friendly
Who reached out to you first?
That's good, I don't think they will interfere
Russia, Austria, and you
Awesome!
How are you planning to open?
Turkey wants to bounce, I'll let him in, not a huge risk in letting him into it if you're opening Lepanto. Austria and I are going to bounce in Galicia, pretty standard. You?
That's perfect!
Just wanted to confirm with you that Russia told me he's planning on bouncing in Galicia? I trust that what you've heard from them is the truth
Hey Germany, just wanna say good luck and hopefully we can be friends!
Hey England, just wanna say good luck and hopefully we can be friends!
Awesome!
Hey France, just wanna say good luck and hopefully we can be friends!
Yeah me too
Yep! That's what he said.
Awesome. Have you heard from Russia or Austria much?
Perfect. Just wanted to double check.
Sounds good! You too, and yeah I'm down for that, I think Turkey and France are some of the best late game allies!
Oh interesting, that's very different than my experience haha
That's true, we can meet up in Italy!
Cheers! I like having friends. You should probably try to get on good terms with Austria.
Hey Turkey, good luck to you too! I'd love to stay on good terms
Absolutely! I look forward to it!
Yeah I'm getting along with Austria pretty well
It's a very different one. Hopefully they're more to be trusted than not
Sounds good
Me too
Yeah, not too much. Are you just gonna stay neutral for now?
That's great. I'm getting along with Russia too but I don't like how noncommital he is. I hope he gets bounced out of Sweden.
Hopefully so!
Have you talked with Italy much?
That's the plan
I would imagine he will
Hopefully.
What are your thoughts on Belgium?
Are you getting along with Germany?
Yep. Have you heard much from them?
I haven't really tried, since they're usually not a huge concern for France early game
Though it's not surprising since I don't interact with them much
I think it goes without saying that I'd like it.
That's fair. I guess we'll see what happens!
Yeah! Let's just hope we both come out of this in a good spot hahaha
Have you heard much from the west? I'm wondering how England will be moving in the north
Yep! At the very least, we know we can trust each other :)
He said he's not planning much beyond taking Norway, but that's it.
Exactly!
That's interesting. Hopefully that means he's friendly with Germany and not looking for conflict in the east
Of course haha, just wondering what you're thinking in that regard
Fingers crossed
I've talked to Italy a little, we agreed to try and stay out of each other's ways.
Gotcha. I talked with Italy some as well and we said we are both gonna stay neutral
Yeah, that seems like a good strategy for Italy. Have you heard anything from Russia?
What do you think Turkey is going to do?
Did they tell you they were going to bounce the Black Sea?
Well I'd like two builds this year. I'm hoping to get Belgium.
That's what they told me
Ok gotcha
Yeah he's just gonna open up standard
Hopefully.
Understood
Fingers crossed! How are you feeling about the Black Sea?
Not really sure yet, but the bounce in Black Sea is much safer for me.
Fair enough!
I'm going for Greece, do you want me to support you into Rumania?
I'm going for Greece, are you going for Tunis?
I'm surprised England opened north
I think I'm on decent terms with him.
Yeah, definitely a good sign for us!
Yep, that's the plan. Are you using your fleet for Greece?
That worked out fairly well!
Great, that worked out fairly well! Do you want to DMZ the Black Sea now?
Are you planning to bounce Russia in Sweden?
Can you support Yorkshire into Belgium?
Yes, I am.
Yup, that's the plan
What do you think France is doing? Is Germany and England both going to Belgium?
Ok, are you planning to go against Russia?
I just wanna know so I can make plans
Great, that worked out fairly well! Any plans for this move?
Yeah, I can do that!
I assume we'll be focusing together on attacking Germany?
I'm going to use Sev to support Ukr-rum and then we'll start moving on Austria next year.
Do you need support into Belgium?
I'm going for Greece, do you need me to support you into Rumania?
I'm going to use Vienna to cover Trieste.
I would like to be in the Black Sea just to make sure I can trust you
Hey Italy, let me know if I can help you with anything
Who are you thinking of siding with, between Austria and Russia?
I haven't decided yet. What are you thinking?
Sounds good to me! Yeah, I'll move to Rum from Ukr and then we'll start moving on Turkey next year.
Looks like things are going well, just be careful with Trieste
I haven't decided yet either
Thanks for the heads up!
Yup! We should make quick work of him.
Thanks Germany! Let me know if you hear anything about the east!
Great!
Excellent! Sounds like a plan!
Just wanted to make sure we were on the same page!
Nah, I'm not. At least, not right now.
Is Italy moving for Tunis or convoying to Greece?
Let me know once you decide. If I'm gonna go with one of them it will probably be easier if I know you are going against the other
Nothing useful, just that Turkey seemed friendly
Ok, we will see what happens
What's your read on France?
Is that ok?
I'm not sure, he hasn't really said anything about it. I'm not sure if he is going for Tunis or not.
I think I'll be fine. I'm moving from Yorkshire to Belgium.
Sounds good, I'll let you know!
Yes we will.
Would you mind if I take Greece for now and we can trade it later?
Awesome
Sounds good
How do you want to proceed after the first year?
I think we should go after France. We can see how the builds shake out.
Agreed
I'd prefer not, why do you want it now?
It's just easier to defend if I have it already
You aren't going to be able to take it this turn anyway and it will be easier if I have it then you if Italy goes for it
Who are you thinking of siding with in the east, between Russia and Turkey?
Just a heads up, I'm going to bounce you in Sweden this turn
I'm taking Norway with a fleet as promised. I think Germany might bounce you out of Sweden.
I know you said you weren't interested in Greece but I'm gonna take it for now so Austria can't have it
I really don't like that idea, we should work together. I'd be willing to help you against England.
No, that makes no sense for either of us. A DMZ in Black Sea would be perfect so we can work together against Austria and Italy.
Thanks, hopefully he doesn't.
I'm trying to work with Russia
Italy is going for Tunis, they have no reason to try and take it now.
Indeed! Are you planning on moving Sev-rum this turn?
I'll be going for Tunis and holding Venice
I'm just looking to keep balance, especially given the south
That's perfectly fine with me, and actually works out better for me since I don't have to commit my fleet in the Ionian Sea
Sounds good, I was just curious since I haven't spoken to Russia much
I wouldn't put it past him.
However, that doesn't mean I'll try to help him if he does.
How's it looking in the east?
Pretty decent, pretty standard start all around. How about you?
Yeah, I agree. As long as you're focused on France or Germany and not me, I'd be happy to help you against Germany.
Yep, I'll be going Ukr-rum with Sev support, pretty standard :)
That'd be great.
Ok. Are we still going against Russia?
Sounds good!
How do I know I can trust you?
You're not in position yet
Are you and Austria planning on bouncing Russia out of Rumania?
That's not what I was planning on doing, why?
Yeah pretty similar, I assume you and Austria are teaming up on Turkey?
Yep, that's the plan! Any plans for your end?
I'm still deciding right now, I'll have to see how this next year plays out first. I'm just glad I don't have to worry about Italy for now
Okay, that's all he told me as well. Turkey also wants to bounce in the Black Sea, which I obviously don't want to do haha.
You can't really, I guess I could let you into the Black Sea this year and trust you'll vacate it next year, but I'd rather not.
Yeah, I'm glad as well!
How do I know you won't take it?
Just wanted to give you the heads up though, England is planning on focusing on Scandinavia
I'm glad to see you and Austria are getting along so well.
Indeed! We're far apart enough that there's no need to worry about an alliance, so there's no reason not to be friendly :)
I agree.
Have you heard much from France or Germany?
Glad to see that we can both be trusted!
I've heard from both. They seem to want to attack each other.
Agreed! How are things looking in the east?
France has been friendly towards me, so I'm not expecting them to be hostile towards me any time soon
Not surprising. If they do, that would leave an opening for you to strike, assuming you're planning to convoy the army to Norway?
It would.
Hopefully good. I'm taking Tunis with my army in Apulia and holding Venice. How about you?
Interesting. I guess that leaves France as the odd one out, but they'll still get two builds
Are you and France working together to stop Germany from getting Belgium?
Sounds good. I'm moving my fleet to Portugal and supporting England into Belgium
Makes sense! I'd love for England to commit to attacking Russia
I'm not sure. I hope not!
I'm hoping to get Belgium. Why?
It would indeed. Are you thinking of doing a Lepanto?
I think it would be smart if England and France worked together to stop Germany from getting it, I'm hoping that's what is going to happen.
That's what France has said, and given that England doesn't need to worry about a Russian attack, I assume that's what's going to happen. We'll see what happens.

It doesn't seem like Germany is going to help you much. If you let France have it, you will eventually be in a battle against them. I haven't talked to France much, but I think they are more likely to help you than Germany.
Yeah, that makes sense.
At the moment I'm not sure. If Austria and Turkey ally, I'll probably have to, but we'll see what happens
Are you planning to move against Turkey? I'm currently working with Russia against them, I think it would be beneficial if we were all working together against them.
Thanks for the insight.
I'd like to see that.
No problem, I just want to see a strong England.
Definitely the plan at the moment. I'll be convoying Apulia to Tunis and holding Venice.
As do I.
I'd imagine you would too
Awesome, I think that will work out well.
Naturally.
I'd also like to see a strong Italy.
A strong Italy would obviously also like to see a strong England :)
Fingers crossed!
Very true.
Austria?
Are you planning to take Trieste?
Austria hasn't been responding to me
Yes, sorry.
Do you want support into Rumania or am I taking Greece?
I'm gonna take Greece for now so Italy doesn't get it
Ok
You can take it back next year and we can switch it out
I haven't decided yet. I might hold since it's a pretty vulnerable position
It will definitely be worth it to take it, we can take Austria pretty quick
Fair point. I'll think about it

AUSTRIA: A SER S F ALB - GRE
ENGLAND: F NTH C A YOR - BEL
FRANCE: A PIC S A YOR - BEL
GERMANY: A RUH S A YOR - BEL
ITALY: F ION C A APU - TUN
RUSSIA: F SEV S A UKR - RUM

messages.message: I mean, it's really up to you, but you'll be much more secure if you don't build in Ankara.
Interesting, I'm glad you stayed cautious
Sorry France, I think I made a mistake
How did Turkey get the Black Sea?
I have no idea, that was very unexpected.
What made you decide to support England into Belgium?
Yeah, given that they have to choose between attacking me or attacking England, I'm not too worried
Very interesting. It makes sense in retrospect since Turkey will be building in Ankara, but I was expecting Sev to support the move to Rum
Do you think they are working with Russia?
That worked out great for you, Italy going for Tunis is great for us!
Agreed
Yeah, I don't know why Turkey would build in Ankara other than to move to Armenia next turn.
That worked out well for you. It's definitely going to be interesting to see where England builds
What are you thinking for builds?
How did you get the Black Sea? Are you going to build in Ankara and move to Armenia?
No I'm building in Smyrna just in case Italy comes after me
Yeah, pretty surprised that Germany decided to support England, I was expecting Germany to bounce him out for sure
England seemed more communicative and I thought it would make sense to keep my border secure. Clearly it was a mistake though. How do you want to go forward?
I'm not planning on building in Ankara
Yeah, that worked out great for us. What is going on with Turkey? I'm surprised they got the Black Sea.
Honestly I'm not sure yet, I'm waiting to see where builds are to make a decision. What are you thinking?
Alright, makes sense. Italy's move to Tunis makes it look like they aren't going for you.
Great!
I'm probably going to go double army, try to secure my northern border
He said he's not planning on building in Ankara, but we'll see. I'll probably have to build in Warsaw.
Are you still planning on going against Russia?
For obvious reasons haha
Either that or try to take Rum with it. I guess we'll have to see what Russia says
I assume that move to the Black Sea wasn't planned?
Yeah, what do you think we should do?
Yeah
I'm building an army in Edinburgh and a fleet in London. I'm thinking an army might be more useful right now.
Haha yes, the build in Warsaw makes sense
I don't know, I will have to see what happens with Italy's build
Makes sense
It will probably be a fleet in Naples
Sounds good. What about me, should I double fleet build and focus on taking down Italy or would you be alright with me building an army in Brest and going after Germany?
Yeah, I don't think I can afford to build in Stp or Mos without England's cooperation, and I don't want to anger him until we've taken out Turkey.
That's smart, a battle against Germany wouldn't be good right now.
Yeah
Nope, but not much I could have done about it. The good news is he didn't move his army to Armenia and he said he's not going to build in Ankara, so hopefully I can sneak in there.
I'm happy to let you into Sweden now though
Have you talked to Italy at all?
I'm surprised that Germany didn't let you have Sweden
I don't think there's much you could have done about it either. At least you still have a pretty strong position
Yeah, I think I'm in pretty good shape for now, we'll just have to see how it plays out.
Not in a while, why?
I'm glad to hear that! What are your thoughts about England?
Fingers crossed!
He says he's going to let me in next turn, and I'd rather not fight him right now. You and Italy are on good terms, is he planning on going for Turkey with us?
Are you planning to build a fleet in Naples?
And what are you planning on building?
I was just curious, he told me he is planning to go for you.
I believe so
I don't know where he is going to go, but I think we are on good terms.
Are you planning to let Russia into Sweden?
I am. Fleet in Naples makes sense to me, since I'll probably need naval support against Turkey
I think so, unless England or France can offer me something in return
Yeah I figured
So are you planning to go for me?
England and France are both pretty reasonable, I'm not sure which way I'll go yet. Probably double army to be safe
Ok, that's smart
Makes sense
How do you want to defend against it?
I'm definitely considering it. It's probably one of my better options given that you're in the Black Sea
Unless you have a better plan
What about you?
Well if you go for me I won't have a reason to help you against Austria
I have to see what Russia is gonna do. If I don't have to worry about you and Italy I can defend against it easily
I'll probably have to build in Warsaw, so I can move my fleet to Sweden and my army to Stp, and be prepared if England makes a move towards Stp.
I'm building in Smyrna so I will easily be able to defend against you
That's good, the Lepanto would be especially effective with Turkey focusing on me.
That makes sense. Have you decided what you're doing in the south?
It all really depends on what Turkey and Austria decide to do, I haven't gotten that far yet. What about you?
I'll probably go double army, not sure where though
Okay, that's probably a good idea.
Cool
If you ever need help, let me know
Thanks, I'll let you know!
Fair enough
Ok, I can defend against it if you are able to defend against Russia
Do you know what Italy is planning to do?
How do you think we should split Turkey's supply centers?
I assume he's going after Turkey
So are you gonna go for it?
I haven't decided yet. I'll let you know when I do
Ok
Well it would make sense for me to get Ankara and Smyrna, since you've gotten the Balkans, but Con and Bul are up for grabs.
Ok, thanks
That makes sense, I'll probably take Bul and Con then
Have you talked to Italy much?

Sounds good, we can figure out the exact details once we get there.

I have talked to Italy a bit, mostly to discuss our plans for Turkey, which we haven't really had to coordinate much on. I'll reach out again, and see what he thinks.
Ok, sounds good
Are you planning to go after Italy?
I'm not sure yet, I haven't decided
I'm still a bit worried about Germany and England
What are your plans for this round? Do you want me to support hold you in Belgium?
Yeah, it's probably smart to be. The fleet in Marseilles is aggressive against Italy.
Probably, though I'm still not completely sure. What are your plans for the east? Are you and Russia planning on going after Turkey?
Yes, I'd like that. Are you going to move Paris to Burgundy?
Yeah, that's my plan. What are you thinking about doing?
Is there any reason why you decided to build in Warsaw?
We haven't decided yet.
I thought I told you that's what I was doing?
I wouldn't be surprised if you and Russia teamed up on Germany soon, it looks like you guys are already kind of set up to do so
Right, but I thought you were building in St. Petersburg
It looks like I'm going to go for it. Sorry to mislead you
Why do you think we are set up to do so?
I'm trying to figure out what to do.
That's fair, I'm assuming you're going to be focusing on taking out Germany?
If so, maybe you can convince Germany to support hold you in Belgium and you could move North Sea to Heligo and London to North Sea?
I don't understand why you would mislead me
What are you thinking about for this turn? We could take Bulgaria by supporting your army in Serbia there. I'd move to Armenia as well, and I'm pretty sure that would mean we take one or the other.

Also, is there anything I could help you with with my army in Warsaw? I had agreed with Germany that I would only build there so I could move my fleet to Sweden and be prepared if England moved to Stp, but that's obviously not what happened haha.
I thought you were planning on letting me into Sweden, but that obviously didn't happen haha. I'm not going to get into a war with you, and I have no intention of fighting you.
